<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="520" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1522,1871]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1703,1727]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">Remarks.</emphasis>
: This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[631,763,1704,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[631,763,1704,1727]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">B. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from the latter by the five longitudinal orange bands on the pronotum; basal apodeme of aedeagus expanded, but not tapering to apex, and aedeagal shaft longer and slightly straighter at middle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
